Deputies proposed to accelerate the entry into force of the law on personal data
If successful, the initiative, the data can not be stored Russians on servers abroad since January 1, 2015
In the State Duma a draft law providing for the transfer of the date of entry into force of the adopted law on personal data of Russians - from 1 September 2016 to 1 January 2015.
The initiative is placed in the base of the legislative activities of the lower chamber.
Its authors were the deputies of the State Duma Vadim Dengin Yaroslav Nilov (LDPR), Evgeny Fedorov ("United Russia"), Vladimir Parahin ("Fair Russia") and Alexander Yushchenko (CPRF).
This change, according to the authors of the initiative, will facilitate a more rapid and effective enforcement of the rights of Russian citizens on the safety of personal data and the secrecy of correspondence in the information and telecommunications networks.
Law, whose entry into force hasten parliament obliges store in Russia Russians personal data processed via the Internet.
It also makes mandatory recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, updating and removal of personal data of citizens of the Russian Federation, in databases located on the territory of Russia, as well as an indication of information on the location of the database.
In addition, the law gives the right to Roskomnadzor court decision to restrict access to the information processed in violation of the Russian legislation in the field of personal data.
The law also proposes the creation of so-called "black lists" of offending sites - automated information system "Register of infringers of personal data."
This law was passed by the State Duma in the summer.
The authors of the bill were Andrei Lugovoi and Vadim Dengin LDPR and the Communist Party, Alexander Yushchenko.
Dengin Yushchenko also among the authors of this bill to postpone the entry into force of the adopted law.
Those who have data centers in the Russian Federation there is no need to pay the rent
Commenting today introduced a bill in the State Duma first deputy head of the Duma Committee on Information Policy, Leonid Levin said that he sees no problems for the postponement of the entry into force of the law on protection of personal data.
According to him, those companies that have a January 1, 2015 will not have their own storage of personal data of Russians in Russia will be able to rent them, such as "u" Rostelecom ", which has repeatedly said that they are willing to provide their servers for rent and already provides its servers in Mail Group, the Western companies that today are already providing their servers. "
"Moreover, there are several independent data centers willing to cooperate in this field," - he added.
"If companies decide to implement the law and continue to work in Russia, I see no problem - they will get the technological possibilities for accommodation" - summed Levin.
The controversial bill
Immediately after the publication of the draft Law of the Russian Association of Electronic Communications expressed concern that the adoption of the bill the Russians no longer be able to use many global Internet services.
In particular, we are talking about the services of online booking air tickets and hotels.
According to the association, "the bill deprives the subjects of personal data - citizens of the Russian Federation the right to manage their own data defining imperative that they record, organize, and so should be provided only in databases located on the territory of the Russian Federation."
In a statement RAEC stresses that more effective measure would be to create a mechanism to inform the user about where the recording, systematization of his personal data.
In this case, he will be able to choose which area will be carried out such actions.
The adoption of these bills on the "localization" of personal data in other countries has led to the maintenance of global services and to significant economic losses.
