The Ministry of Communications has proposed to allocate 250 million rubles broadcasting company "Crimea"
The Ministry of Communications has proposed to allocate in 2014 from the federal budget 250 million rubles independent non-profit organization "TV and Radio Company" Crimea "."
This is stated in the draft resolution of the Government, prepared by the Office, seen "to Lenta.ru."
According to the explanatory memorandum to the draft, subsidies from the federal budget will be directed "towards the cost of creating the conditions for a large-scale media coverage of the socio-economic situation and development of the modern information space in the Republic of Crimea, including the purchase of equipment."
In particular, for the money is supposed to convert hardware-studio block, video walls, the central hardware and videoservernuyu.
It is also planned acquisition of mobile television station and satellite transmitter.
In addition, the company will pay the allocated funds the use of fiber-optic communication line (FOCL) and the renovation of energy.
Subsidies will be provided within the means of the federal budget allocated to the Ministry of Communications.
National Broadcasting Company "Crimea" was created in 1959, broadcasts in seven languages: Ukrainian, Russian, Crimean Tatar, German, Greek, Bulgarian and Armenian.
Today, television and radio coverage of the television signal is more than 75 percent of the peninsula.
In 2011, "TV and Radio Company" Crimea "," received a license for television broadcasting in digital format.
